2 Program Execution [b]reak Sets a breakpoint on either a function, a line given by a line number, or the instruction located at a particular address.

If you do not have access to the source code of a function and wish to set a breakpoint on a is the name of particular instruction, call the procedure); this command will allow you to see the memory address of each instruction. See section 4 for further information.

[s]tep Steps through a single line of code. Steps into function calls.
(gdb) break main Breakpoint 1 at 0x8049377: file main.c, line 34. (gdb) r

[s]tep[i] Steps through a single x86 instruction. Steps into calls.

[n]ext Steps through a single line of code. Steps over function calls.
